FP:<br />
Play what you can with your opening hand.  Stop at site 2.  Next turn play Treebeard.  Move to site 3, stop - play Theoden.  Try and not play a Spear to Theoden - get one to Eomer and Eowyn and possible a Rider.  From this point on it just depends on what your opponent has - You should be alright, even though you have no archery.  The only minions that really hurt this deck are Uruks.  (if you can play with rare Eomer and Eowyn)<br />
Minions:<br />
Haha - This is the most unorganized shadow side I have ever composed.  So don&#39;t hold it against me.  Basically all it does is beat up and kill FP companions.  Weary and Many Riddles are effective against Aragorn and Rare Eomer - since they are the strongest companions.  Watch out for Gondorian rangers and RofI - I haven&#39;t played against many of them so I don&#39;t know how to defend agaisnt it.  But I am sure it should be too hard with these minions.<br />
